SMART ROOM AUTOMATION USING ESP32

Abstract:
This project automates home appliances using an ESP32 microcontroller. It controls lights and fans through Wi-Fi, providing convenience and energy efficiency.

Components:
• ESP32
• Relay Module
• Breadboard
• Jumper Wires
• LED
• Fan

Software:
• Arduino IDE

Working:
The ESP32 receives commands through serial/Wi-Fi and switches the connected appliances using relay modules.

Advantages:
• Easy to use
• Low cost
• Energy efficient
• IoT based

Future Scope:
• Mobile App Control
• Voice Assistant
• Temperature and Humidity Monitoring

Conclusion:
The project demonstrates how IoT can automate home appliances using ESP32.